http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Implement-panel-recommendations-%E2%80%99/article14013121.ece

Amarnath Patil, MLC, has urged the State government to implement the recommendations of the Kumar Naik Committee report to “undo the injustice” in the pay fixation of the principals and lecturers in PU colleges and end the disparity in their wages.Mr. Patil met Chief Minister Siddaramaiah on Monday and submitted a memorandum seeking early implementation of the report.MemorandumIn the memorandum, he said that the committee headed by Mr. Naik, the then Principal Secretary, Primary and Higher Education, had made many recommendations and the government was not showing any interest in adopting the report even after four years.